00:22:30,021 --> 00:22:31,601
Can I talk to him now?

238
00:22:33,061 --> 00:22:35,535
-You're talking to him already. Here he is.
-You?

239
00:22:35,559 --> 00:22:38,035
-Yes I am.
-I'm very sorry, please excuse...

240
00:22:38,059 --> 00:22:39,518
Just take a seat, it's alright.

241
00:22:45,476 --> 00:22:47,685
Say, why are you following me?

242
00:22:48,185 --> 00:22:50,725
If you tell me where you're heading,
I'll lead the way.

243
00:22:51,686 --> 00:22:55,850
-What do you want from me?
-A good day. No?

244
00:22:57,934 --> 00:23:00,770
Mrs., you're a model, aren't you?

245
00:23:00,822 --> 00:23:03,936
-Me? Why?
-The way you dress.

246
00:23:06,226 --> 00:23:08,433
Now, enough with this following business.

247
00:23:08,726 --> 00:23:11,517
I think so, too. If this doesn't stop,
we'll soon be in Schönbrunn.

248
00:23:12,601 --> 00:23:18,101
Mrs., a single word
and I'm gone in a second.

249
00:23:18,604 --> 00:23:22,767
-So, what is it?
-When will I see you again?

250
00:23:23,477 --> 00:23:26,994
-Never!
-Can't you give me a more precise date?

251
00:23:27,018 --> 00:23:29,577
That's precise enough, isn't it?

252
00:23:29,601 --> 00:23:31,579
It isn't.
Mrs., I have to ask you something.

253
00:23:31,603 --> 00:23:34,455
Mrs., why all this chasing around?

254
00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:39,517
♫ Even if you're moving too fast
even if I'm not catching up

255
00:23:39,603 --> 00:23:44,744
♫ Your perfume is ecstasy for my nose

256
00:23:44,768 --> 00:23:49,979
♫ As long as this is the case
you're with me, even when far away

257
00:23:51,809 --> 00:23:56,851
♫ My dearest I'm in love with your perfume

258
00:23:57,351 --> 00:24:02,059
♫ Because it puts me in the right mood

259
00:24:02,309 --> 00:24:06,600
♫ I don't know what it is,
I only realize

260
00:24:07,562 --> 00:24:11,475
♫ There's something, there's something,
there's something

261
00:24:12,684 --> 00:24:16,684
♫ My dearest, I'm so fond of your perfume

262
00:24:17,392 --> 00:24:21,892
♫ It brings us together,
even when you're far away

263
00:24:22,393 --> 00:24:27,187
♫ It smells of kisses that only happen once

264
00:24:29,063 --> 00:24:33,186
♫ I'm in love with your perfume

265
00:24:34,642 --> 00:24:38,645
♫ My dearest I'm in love with your perfume

266
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:42,768
♫ Because it puts me in the right mood

267
00:24:43,143 --> 00:24:46,702
♫ I don't know what it is,
I only realize

268
00:24:46,726 --> 00:24:47,726
Taxi!

269
00:24:47,809 --> 00:24:50,933
♫ There's something, there's something,
there's something

270
00:24:52,142 --> 00:24:55,058
I won't let you leave until you tell me
if you're coming.

271
00:24:55,101 --> 00:24:56,976
-Yes or no.
-Maybe.

272
00:24:57,230 --> 00:24:58,477
She's coming.

273
00:25:00,559 --> 00:25:05,100
♫ It smells of kisses that only happen once

274
00:25:05,726 --> 00:25:07,476
Tonight at the Cobenzl!

275
00:25:07,685 --> 00:25:11,725
♫ I'm in love with your perfume

276
00:25:12,393 --> 00:25:14,559
Please come in.

277
00:25:16,517 --> 00:25:19,434
Well, it's settled!

278
00:25:19,726 --> 00:25:23,808
It is? That makes me very happy!

279
00:25:23,851 --> 00:25:25,143
Me too!

280
00:25:25,234 --> 00:25:26,283
We too!

281
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:31,327
It's just... things are moving so fast!

282
00:25:31,351 --> 00:25:33,018
All of a sudden!

283
00:25:34,017 --> 00:25:37,810
I'd like to tell my mother.
May I use the phone?

284
00:25:38,017 --> 00:25:42,101
-Well...
-Of course! Over here! There's the phone!

285
00:25:43,018 --> 00:25:44,475
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

286
00:25:46,934 --> 00:25:49,893
Hello? Hello?

287
00:25:53,872 --> 00:25:55,101
No one's on the line.

288
00:25:55,976 --> 00:25:58,119
Oh yes, naturally.

289
00:25:58,143 --> 00:26:01,577
-What do you mean?
-Let me for a minute, I'll deal with it.

290
00:26:01,601 --> 00:26:07,351
Hello... Hello!... I don't get it.

291
00:26:10,850 --> 00:26:12,642
HOME
OPERATOR

292
00:26:13,143 --> 00:26:14,143
What's that?

293
00:26:15,768 --> 00:26:19,493
-Slow line.
-Slow line? Oh, now I get it.

294
00:26:19,517 --> 00:26:22,851
The slow line is busy,
I'll transfer to the short one.

295
00:26:34,101 --> 00:26:35,560
Hello? Hello!

296
00:26:36,268 --> 00:26:41,559
-Operator speaking.
-Mrs., please put me through to 30206.

297
00:26:41,767 --> 00:26:43,893
30206. In a moment.

298
00:26:50,475 --> 00:26:56,268
-Hello mother?
-Hello, Fischer and Weber speaking.

299
00:26:56,310 --> 00:26:58,601
-Whom am I speaking to?
-Fischer and Weber.

300
00:26:59,018 --> 00:27:01,227
Wrong number. Please hang up.

301
00:27:01,351 --> 00:27:02,726
Goddamn it!

302
00:27:04,643 --> 00:27:09,810
-Mrs., I got the wrong number.
-I'm sorry, won't happen again.

303
00:27:10,308 --> 00:27:15,851
-30206, if I may.
-30206. In a moment.

304
00:27:19,976 --> 00:27:22,101
The line is busy.

305
00:27:27,468 --> 00:27:28,468
What's this?

306
00:27:31,434 --> 00:27:33,425
Have you gone mad?

307
00:27:39,768 --> 00:27:43,725
What's with the lad out there?
He must be off his rockers.

308
00:27:44,017 --> 00:27:45,975
I can't get a connection.

309
00:27:46,975 --> 00:27:48,893
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm Wiesinger.

310
00:27:49,475 --> 00:27:53,225
Say, I went to the advertisement agency.
That goldfish also swam away.

311
00:27:53,935 --> 00:27:55,183
It's over, we're finished.

312
00:27:57,100 --> 00:27:59,684
May I introduce: Miss Longing.

313
00:28:00,518 --> 00:28:05,267
-Wait... You're Longing...?
-...202!

314
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:10,101
That's... That's marvelous.
That's wonderful.

315
00:28:10,725 --> 00:28:12,184
-Get a chair for the lady.
-Will do.

316
00:28:12,351 --> 00:28:17,351
May I offer a lemonade... a lemon...
a cold glass of water...

317
00:28:17,475 --> 00:28:19,642
-No, thank you.
-At least take a seat.

318
00:28:20,184 --> 00:28:21,226
That's amazing.

319
00:28:21,350 --> 00:28:26,476
-So everything's settled?
-So far yes. About the specifics...

320
00:28:26,934 --> 00:28:29,934
Yes, about the salary.

321
00:28:30,726 --> 00:28:35,350
-What sal...
-About the salary, naturally.

322
00:28:35,518 --> 00:28:37,909
Of course, the salary is important for you.

323
00:28:37,933 --> 00:28:39,826
-It is.
-Of course.

324
00:28:39,850 --> 00:28:42,018
Well, what were you thinking of?

325
00:28:43,017 --> 00:28:47,560
I thought... maybe... 100.

326
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:51,868
-100
-50... Maybe 150!

327
00:28:51,892 --> 00:28:56,975
150! This we can do, can we?

328
00:28:57,309 --> 00:28:59,351
-Granted!
-Yes, yes...

329
00:29:02,018 --> 00:29:05,326
And while you're in a good mood,
I've got another request.

330
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:08,435
Another request? Granted, too!
We're very generous.

331
00:29:09,268 --> 00:29:11,685
Can I have one month's pay in advance?

332
00:29:14,683 --> 00:29:19,475
-A... Advance?
-Gra... Granted, of course.

333
00:29:20,310 --> 00:29:22,434
He's the one granting the advances.

334
00:29:23,642 --> 00:29:24,726
-Splitter!
-Yes?

335
00:29:25,019 --> 00:29:28,476
Take the lady to the office
and show her the rooms.

336
00:29:28,684 --> 00:29:31,267
We'll take care of the advance later on,
of course.

337
00:29:31,517 --> 00:29:34,935
Out of the way. May I?
I'm sure you'll like it here.

338
00:29:35,267 --> 00:29:36,994
Did I do well with the phone?

339
00:29:37,018 --> 00:29:38,409
-Splitter!
-Yes?

340
00:29:38,433 --> 00:29:40,159
-Come on!
-Oh yes...

341
00:29:40,183 --> 00:29:43,643
Behave yourself.
No ring ring and stuff like that.

342
00:29:45,142 --> 00:29:49,368
Say, moron,
you're promising her 150 schillings?

343
00:29:49,392 --> 00:29:52,034
-What do you call me? A moron?
-Yes I do.

344
00:29:52,058 --> 00:29:53,726
-What are you, then?
-Your partner.

345
00:29:55,309 --> 00:29:58,244
You almost blew it right no. Super-moron!

346
00:29:58,268 --> 00:30:01,893
-Beautiful rooms.
-Yes, they are.

347
00:30:02,726 --> 00:30:06,518
-I like it very much.
-Glad to hear.

348
00:30:06,642 --> 00:30:10,577
I don't get it. What does she need 150
schillings, being a millionaire's daughter?

349
00:30:10,601 --> 00:30:15,101
That's just her quirk. One flies over the
ocean, the other collects Maybugs...

350
00:30:15,309 --> 00:30:16,602
So what will she do in December?

351
00:30:16,883 --> 00:30:18,559
And this one wants to earn her own money.

352
00:30:18,726 --> 00:30:21,226
And so she should! But not our money!

353
00:30:21,435 --> 00:30:23,702
Say, is it always that quiet here?

354
00:30:23,726 --> 00:30:26,601
Yes... yes, how could you think that...

355
00:30:26,726 --> 00:30:33,601
Sometimes... it's slower... sometimes not
that much... sometimes not at all...

356
00:30:34,018 --> 00:30:37,059
But that doesn't mean anything,
it's just because...

357
00:30:37,517 --> 00:30:42,035
...because... today is Friday, the 13th!

358
00:30:42,059 --> 00:30:45,351
-Is that so?
-Oh yes, people are superstitious.

359
00:30:45,893 --> 00:30:51,518
On some Fridays I...
almost look forward to Sundays.

360
00:30:52,018 --> 00:30:55,225
So how can we get hold of 150 schillings?

361
00:30:56,642 --> 00:31:00,643
Do you know what we've sold
since yesterday? A toothbrush!

362
00:31:02,326 --> 00:31:06,853
In installments.
And you want 150... Ridiculous!

363
00:31:08,893 --> 00:31:10,976
Say, Bobby, come here.

364
00:31:12,185 --> 00:31:15,643
-I've got an idea.
-Unbelievable!

365
00:31:16,100 --> 00:31:20,201
-But don't get mad.
-On the contrary. A rare occasion anyway.

366
00:31:20,225 --> 00:31:21,267
So what is it?

367
00:31:21,643 --> 00:31:23,892
I... I want to sell the ring.

368
00:31:24,768 --> 00:31:29,059
This ring? That I gave to you as a present?
You should be ashamed.

369
00:31:29,101 --> 00:31:31,702
My friend, beggars can't be choosers.

370
00:31:31,726 --> 00:31:34,077
That's just a phrase.
You can't sell the ring.

371
00:31:34,101 --> 00:31:36,036
And where can we find the money?

372
00:31:36,060 --> 00:31:38,701
I don't care. This ring you can't sell.

373
00:31:38,725 --> 00:31:40,418
-I have to.
-No you don't.

374
00:31:40,442 --> 00:31:43,850
-I will.
-You won't. I forbid it.

375
00:31:44,267 --> 00:31:47,976
-And why?
-Because... it's a forged rock.

376
00:31:48,393 --> 00:31:50,243
To make it short: a solid business.

377
00:31:50,267 --> 00:31:52,952
I can see that. So this is the register?

378
00:31:52,976 --> 00:31:55,851
That's the register, but it doesn't work.
Out of order.

379
00:31:55,975 --> 00:31:59,202
But here you have the list, for comparison.

380
00:31:59,226 --> 00:32:03,368
In line one there's Eau de Cologne,
in line two there's lavender...

381
00:32:03,392 --> 00:32:05,035
-You there!
-One moment!

382
00:32:05,059 --> 00:32:06,453
And in line three there's red...

383
00:32:06,477 --> 00:32:09,827
-Oh, hello!
-Where are the bosses?

384
00:32:09,851 --> 00:32:15,576
My bosses? In there. But they can't be
disturbed right now. An important meeting.

385
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,744
-I have to talk to them.
-Think about it, won't you...

386
00:32:17,768 --> 00:32:20,059
Not when money is involved.

387
00:32:20,517 --> 00:32:22,868
Be reasonable, you can't barge in like...

388
00:32:22,892 --> 00:32:26,142
-Who was that?
-Him? He's a money man.

389
00:32:26,267 --> 00:32:31,102
He wants to force his capital on us.
But we don't need it.

390
00:32:31,643 --> 00:32:35,100
I you won't pay this minute,
I'll tear down the building today.

391
00:32:35,183 --> 00:32:39,034
-That's unpleasant, isn't it Harry?
-I'll say.

392
00:32:39,058 --> 00:32:44,975
Then I guess we'll have to... well...

393
00:32:45,684 --> 00:32:51,017
Dear Property manager, can I offer a pawn?

394
00:32:51,377 --> 00:32:57,185
-A pawn?
-Yes, a souvenir, from a true friend.

395
00:32:57,933 --> 00:33:03,535
All right. But if you won't pay tomorrow,
your ring is gone.

396
00:33:03,559 --> 00:33:06,076
Well... well, what can we do.

397
00:33:06,100 --> 00:33:07,767
-Bye.
-Go with god.

398
00:33:09,976 --> 00:33:13,017
Don't you pout.
I'll return exactly the same ring to you.

399
00:33:13,393 --> 00:33:14,726
-See you!
-See you!

400
00:33:18,517 --> 00:33:19,517
One moment, please.

401
00:33:19,976 --> 00:33:22,994
A forged ring can be useful, too.

402
00:33:23,018 --> 00:33:24,952
So what's going on?
Are we out on the street.

403
00:33:24,976 --> 00:33:27,159
-For now we're fine.
-Thank god.

404
00:33:27,183 --> 00:33:29,286
If only we had money for the advance.

405
00:33:29,310 --> 00:33:33,137
-An advance? For me?
-For you? For the girl, of course.

406
00:33:33,309 --> 00:33:37,183
-For the millionairess!
-Advance...

407
00:33:39,558 --> 00:33:46,059
What's going on, what's going on.
Who do you think you are?

408
00:33:49,561 --> 00:33:51,826
-Paul!
-Magda!

409
00:33:51,850 --> 00:33:55,393
-Paul, listen, I got the job!
-How wonderful.

410
00:33:55,767 --> 00:33:58,393
-So what is it you will be doing?
-I'll be a salesgirl.

411
00:33:59,684 --> 00:34:01,951
-I'll be your first customer, then.
-You are?

412
00:34:01,975 --> 00:34:04,684
I need a dozen razor blades for my boss.

413
00:34:04,809 --> 00:34:06,684
Marvelous, I'll get them for you.
Follow me.

414
00:34:11,809 --> 00:34:13,767
Here are the razor blades.

415
00:34:14,017 --> 00:34:18,726
-But this is a pack of 120!
-Doesn't matter. They're always useful.

416
00:34:19,560 --> 00:34:21,726
-Maybe a cream?
-For my shoes?

417
00:34:21,975 --> 00:34:26,143
No, for your face. Smell this! Nice cream.

418
00:34:26,901 --> 00:34:29,852
You won't find anything here.
What's this?

419
00:34:29,978 --> 00:34:33,119
-Nothing, unfortunately.
-I thought so.

420
00:34:33,143 --> 00:34:35,059
160 schillings altogether.

421
00:34:35,518 --> 00:34:38,810
160 schillings! That's something else.

422
00:34:39,187 --> 00:34:42,308
For this kind of money,
I should've bought a new tire.

423
00:34:42,417 --> 00:34:44,142
This here is much more important.

424
00:34:44,809 --> 00:34:46,226
-One moment!
-What is it?

425
00:34:47,051 --> 00:34:51,243
Ms. Wurmser owes 300 schillings
since three months ago.

426
00:34:51,267 --> 00:34:54,392
-This is it!
-No it ain't!

427
00:34:54,684 --> 00:34:58,392
I already collected
the 300 schillings myself.

428
00:34:58,767 --> 00:35:00,683
-And where are they now?
-Here.

429
00:35:02,393 --> 00:35:03,726
-Very nice.
-Isn't it?

430
00:35:04,142 --> 00:35:07,243
-Very nice.
-What's that? How dare you...

431
00:35:07,267 --> 00:35:08,702
There's only one thing left to do.

432
00:35:08,726 --> 00:35:12,435
One of us has to go out and tell her
that we don't pay advances on principle.

433
00:35:12,768 --> 00:35:14,476
Very well. I'm going out and you tell her.

434
00:35:16,142 --> 00:35:17,808
Too bad about Ms. Wurmser.

435
00:35:19,767 --> 00:35:22,851
Say, where should I put the money?
The register doesn't work.

436
00:35:23,059 --> 00:35:25,477
-Where does this money come from?
-I collected it.

437
00:35:26,058 --> 00:35:29,100
-How did you collect it?
-For the merchandise I sold.

438
00:35:29,683 --> 00:35:32,726
-Someone bought something from us?
-Naturally.

439
00:35:32,892 --> 00:35:34,495
It's not all that natural...

440
00:35:34,519 --> 00:35:37,702
Mrs., we're very sorry,
your advance can't...

441
00:35:37,726 --> 00:35:41,600
...be held back any longer.
150 schillings, wasn't it?

442
00:35:41,684 --> 00:35:44,185
-Yes.
-Of course we'll have to subtract the tax.

443
00:35:44,351 --> 00:35:45,494
-Splitter!
-Yes?

444
00:35:45,518 --> 00:35:47,768
-Hand over the tax table.
-The tax table.

445
00:35:48,059 --> 00:35:49,517
-We have to, unfortunately...

446
00:35:50,351 --> 00:35:54,726
So that makes... No! That's the one from
yesterday, it's no longer valid today.

447
00:35:54,767 --> 00:35:57,411
Sorry, my mistake.

448
00:35:57,435 --> 00:35:59,100
Not your first one.

449
00:35:59,809 --> 00:36:07,368
Tax on income, unemployment, bachelorhood,
crisis, salary, insurance, labor, welfare.

450
00:36:07,392 --> 00:36:10,643
Altogether that makes...
We'll come out just about even in the end.

451
00:36:12,226 --> 00:36:14,309
-You can't do that.
-Why not? She's got millions.

452
00:36:16,437 --> 00:36:21,605
So, 150 schillings, right?
Here you go, tax-free.

453
00:36:21,768 --> 00:36:23,851
Thanks a million. Thanks.

454
00:36:25,605 --> 00:36:29,813
She really took it.
Well, still 10 schillings left.

455
00:36:30,350 --> 00:36:32,725
For my partner... net gain.

456
00:36:33,020 --> 00:36:35,518
A gentleman from head to toe.

457
00:36:36,241 --> 00:36:40,686
1,2,3,4,5,6,7 This one is old, but rich.

458
00:36:41,101 --> 00:36:45,600
1,2,3,4,5,6,7 king of spades,
jack of spaces, ace of spades.

459
00:36:46,101 --> 00:36:49,356
Three black ones... A negro?

460
00:36:51,143 --> 00:36:55,914
No, auntie, he isn't a negro. He isn't old,
either. Aside from that, you got it.

461
00:36:55,938 --> 00:36:58,600
If you don't pay, I will cut the light.

462
00:36:59,517 --> 00:37:04,726
-You simply can't to that.
-Oh, it's very simple.

463
00:37:09,092 --> 00:37:11,892
The display window needs much more light.

464
00:37:12,776 --> 00:37:16,909
More light? Only recently,
we installed marvelous effect lighting.

465
00:37:16,933 --> 00:37:19,643
-You did?
-Effect lighting! Look for yourself.

466
00:37:24,933 --> 00:37:29,017
I don't get it. What's going on?

467
00:37:29,362 --> 00:37:34,143
My friend, think it over. There's a
millionairess sitting outside.

468
00:37:34,604 --> 00:37:38,434
-So make her pay!
-She's not supposed to know!

469
00:37:42,021 --> 00:37:45,393
-By the way, how much is the bill?
-80 schillings.

470
00:37:45,643 --> 00:37:50,851
80 schillings. Well, turn on the light for
