00:56:17,310 --> 00:56:21,159
Marvelous. Tell her to see us in the office
for a moment.

709
00:56:21,183 --> 00:56:23,785
-She's with a customer right now.
-Then you will cover for her.

710
00:56:23,809 --> 00:56:26,933
-I don't know. That one guy didn't like me.
-I can relate.

711
00:56:31,311 --> 00:56:35,577
One moment, one moment.
We'll make sure to deliver all of this.

712
00:56:35,601 --> 00:56:37,911
-In person?
-You can bet on that.

713
00:56:37,935 --> 00:56:40,468
-See you later, then.
-See you later.

714
00:56:41,058 --> 00:56:44,910
One moment, now it's my turn.
Miss, out there, in the show window...

715
00:56:44,934 --> 00:56:47,034
Sorry, the bosses want you in the office.

716
00:56:47,058 --> 00:56:48,892
-But I'm with customers!
-I'll cover for you.

717
00:56:49,059 --> 00:56:51,409
-One moment, please.
-Miss, please stay!

718
00:56:51,433 --> 00:56:54,933
-Sir how can I help you?
-You can't, I already told you that.

719
00:56:55,184 --> 00:56:56,767
Disgusting evasiveness. Goodbye.

720
00:56:57,393 --> 00:56:59,900
-See you.
-I knew he doesn't like me.

721
00:57:00,143 --> 00:57:01,809
-Good morning!
-Good morning!

722
00:57:02,021 --> 00:57:06,894
-You want to talk to me?
-My partner needs to tell you something.

723
00:57:08,101 --> 00:57:11,035
-Correct?
-Yes, correct, I...

724
00:57:11,059 --> 00:57:15,434
...he's a bit shy. I hope you understand.

725
00:57:18,850 --> 00:57:20,188
Won't you take a seat?

726
00:57:22,975 --> 00:57:29,687
-It's just...
-Now he can talk more freely. Am I right?

727
00:57:32,767 --> 00:57:33,767
Well?

728
00:57:34,018 --> 00:57:41,726
Well... I... I'm supposed to...

729
00:57:42,314 --> 00:57:44,726
-I'd like to ask you something.
-Go on!

730
00:57:45,226 --> 00:57:48,894
I wanted to tell you something
that is very close to my heart.

731
00:57:51,687 --> 00:57:54,100
-But we just met.
-Yes.

732
00:57:54,601 --> 00:57:57,327
-Two days ago.
-I said that, too.

733
00:57:57,351 --> 00:58:00,577
My partner talked me into it, though.

734
00:58:00,601 --> 00:58:06,100
-Talked you into it?
-Yes, because I was afraid to tell you.

735
00:58:06,308 --> 00:58:08,559
To be honest, I'm afraid even now.

736
00:58:10,393 --> 00:58:15,494
I think I already know.

737
00:58:15,518 --> 00:58:20,684
Really? Thank heavens, that's a relief.

738
00:58:22,017 --> 00:58:29,076
-So... can I hope?
-I have to talk to my mother, first.

739
00:58:29,100 --> 00:58:33,683
Do that! When can I expect an answer?

740
00:58:34,267 --> 00:58:38,673
-Is it that urgent?
-Yes, very urgent.

741
00:58:40,525 --> 00:58:43,456
Maybe I'll see you tonight? I'll call you.

742
00:58:43,480 --> 00:58:44,934
-Deal?
-Deal!

743
00:58:45,893 --> 00:58:48,767
-You really are charming. Thanks a lot!
-You're welcome.

744
00:58:48,893 --> 00:58:53,267
Miss, if you allow, might I ask

745
00:58:54,226 --> 00:58:57,062
for an advance right now?

746
00:59:05,893 --> 00:59:10,309
Splitter, Splitter... I'm so happy!

747
00:59:15,101 --> 00:59:19,892
-What's that?
-Me... I...

748
00:59:23,768 --> 00:59:26,226
What's going on? Did you talk to her?

749
00:59:26,933 --> 00:59:29,059
-Yes.
-And did she give you something?

750
00:59:29,560 --> 00:59:32,518
-Yes, a kiss.
-What are you saying?

751
00:59:33,433 --> 00:59:37,184
You know, I think I proposed to her.

752
00:59:38,142 --> 00:59:43,142
-You were supposed to ask for a loan.
-I did. But she misunderstood.

753
00:59:43,561 --> 00:59:47,768
-And now?
-And now we go on a date.

754
00:59:47,934 --> 00:59:52,226
How nice. You'll tell her then.
And no misunderstandings this time.

755
00:59:52,310 --> 00:59:53,963
-Nothing doing?
-Sorry?

756
00:59:53,987 --> 00:59:58,201
-Now that I know that she loves me I can't.
-Is that so? I'll tell her, then.

757
00:59:58,225 --> 01:00:02,453
-Hey, hey, I forbid it!
-I'll do it anyway.

758
01:00:02,851 --> 01:00:06,577
-I'll make sure you don't.
-No chance. Want to take a bet?

759
01:00:06,601 --> 01:00:09,851
-We'll see.
-We'll see, exactly. We'll...

760
01:00:10,392 --> 01:00:11,976
-Kitty!
-Bobby!

761
01:00:12,517 --> 01:00:14,517
What brings you here?

762
01:00:15,522 --> 01:00:18,518
I want to get to know you in your
field of action.

763
01:00:18,684 --> 01:00:24,101
That's sweet of... Splitter, please
go and find out what time it is.

764
01:00:26,101 --> 01:00:29,559
-It's nice here.
-It is? Do you like it?

765
01:00:29,683 --> 01:00:33,143
Yes, indeed. So, what do you have on offer?

766
01:00:33,517 --> 01:00:39,104
My lady, let's see. Our own make,
available in all sizes and prize levels.

767
01:00:39,143 --> 01:00:40,851
Oh, how beautiful.

768
01:00:42,894 --> 01:00:44,767
COURT OF EXECUTION, VIENNA

769
01:00:48,435 --> 01:00:52,726
-This must be your trademark.
-Yes, our trademark.

770
01:00:54,733 --> 01:00:57,897
What kind of funny animal is this?

771
01:00:58,058 --> 01:01:00,451
-That's a vulture.
-A vulture?

772
01:01:00,475 --> 01:01:03,772
Yes, there's one of them on all of our
bottles. How many do you want?

773
01:01:04,059 --> 01:01:11,308
Not a single one. I came by to tell you I'm
free tonight and want to go out with you.

774
01:01:11,892 --> 01:01:14,077
-Tonight won't do.
-Why not?

775
01:01:14,101 --> 01:01:19,953
Tonight I'll have to take inventory.
I'll be busy all night.

776
01:01:20,517 --> 01:01:28,392
I'm sorry about that, poor you.
I'll have to think of you all night, then.

777
01:01:30,475 --> 01:01:33,286
-Kitty, you must change perfumes.
-Why?

778
01:01:33,310 --> 01:01:35,328
That one's dangerous for me.

779
01:01:35,352 --> 01:01:41,393
♫ My dearest I'm in love with your perfume

780
01:01:42,142 --> 01:01:47,308
♫ Because it puts me in the right mood

781
01:01:47,935 --> 01:01:53,396
♫ I don't know what it is,
I only realize

782
01:01:53,767 --> 01:01:58,560
♫ There's something, there's something,
there's something

783
01:01:59,018 --> 01:02:04,312
♫ My dearest, I'm so fond of your perfume

784
01:02:05,184 --> 01:02:10,351
♫ It brings us together,
even when you're far away

785
01:02:10,852 --> 01:02:16,850
♫ It smells of kisses that only happen once

786
01:02:21,602 --> 01:02:25,977
♫ I'm in love with your perfume

787
01:02:38,434 --> 01:02:42,747
I don't like you going out
with your boss at night.

788
01:02:42,771 --> 01:02:48,960
But mother, if you only knew him.
He's so harmless.

789
01:02:48,984 --> 01:02:50,892
Those are the worst, believe me, I know.

790
01:02:56,144 --> 01:03:01,410
I can't go like this, anyway. My god,
nothing to wear.

791
01:03:01,434 --> 01:03:03,868
What do you mean?
Your blue dress is very nice.

792
01:03:03,892 --> 01:03:06,744
-No, I can't wear that.
-Why?

793
01:03:06,768 --> 01:03:08,494
It's way too short.

794
01:03:08,518 --> 01:03:12,517
Oh, I forgot. These days,
long dresses are in style again.

795
01:03:14,143 --> 01:03:18,183
Wait a minute! I got an idea!

796
01:03:24,726 --> 01:03:26,226
Well, what about this one?

797
01:03:26,726 --> 01:03:28,744
-Isn't this grandma's ball dress?
-Yes, it is.

798
01:03:28,768 --> 01:03:31,476
-And I'm supposed to wear it?
-It's all the rage now!

799
01:03:32,272 --> 01:03:36,142
-But mother, that won't work.
-Wait and see!

800
01:04:15,684 --> 01:04:18,451
Say Harry, where are you going to meet her?

801
01:04:18,475 --> 01:04:20,017
So we won't end up at the same place.

802
01:04:20,269 --> 01:04:25,267
-We're going to the Moulin Rouge.
-The Moulin Rouge, interesting. Have fun.

803
01:04:26,142 --> 01:04:29,518
-One moment, did you hear that?
-What are you saying?

804
01:04:30,268 --> 01:04:32,768
-Didn't you hear it?
-You and your jokes.

805
01:04:33,309 --> 01:04:36,085
-There's something going on in there.
-Then take a look!

806
01:04:36,109 --> 01:04:38,933
-I'm afraid.
-What a hero.

807
01:04:39,142 --> 01:04:42,559
You go. You're the stronger one.

808
01:04:46,433 --> 01:04:48,017
So, who did win the bet?

809
01:04:49,518 --> 01:04:54,350
I was never smarter. And now I'm going to
get money from the millionairess.

810
01:04:55,309 --> 01:04:57,268
Do not get bored in the meantime.

811
01:05:05,560 --> 01:05:07,103
Open up, scoundrel!

812
01:05:09,142 --> 01:05:11,354
Don't forget to bring out the shoes.

813
01:05:16,475 --> 01:05:22,812
-Well, isn't this lovely?
-Yes, very modern.

814
01:05:23,058 --> 01:05:26,517
And at the same time,
just like in the olden days.

815
01:07:35,229 --> 01:07:38,476
That dress!
I've rarely seen anything so sweet.

816
01:07:39,100 --> 01:07:43,850
-Do you really like it?
-All I can say is: cheers!

817
01:07:45,642 --> 01:07:46,642
Waiter!

818
01:07:47,175 --> 01:07:50,368
-Won't you tell me already about...
-...the waiter? He'll be here in a moment.

819
01:07:50,392 --> 01:07:52,786
-No, I...
-Yes, he will. Just a little...

820
01:07:52,810 --> 01:07:54,767
I'm talking about your partner!

821
01:07:55,216 --> 01:08:01,119
Oh, you're talking about Harry. Well, as
I told you, he is indisposed,

822
01:08:01,143 --> 01:08:03,952
and he asked me to fill in for him,
as far as...

823
01:08:03,976 --> 01:08:06,660
Are you saying he won't show up at all?

824
01:08:06,684 --> 01:08:09,852
He will!
As soon as he manages to free himself up.

825
01:08:19,601 --> 01:08:22,643
Are you that unhappy about the substitute?

826
01:08:24,601 --> 01:08:27,142
-You aren't? Well then, cheers!
-Cheers!

827
01:08:29,568 --> 01:08:33,475
-My friend Harry talked to you today.
-Yes, he did.

828
01:08:33,808 --> 01:08:37,308
-And while doing so, he...
-Yes, he did.

829
01:08:37,683 --> 01:08:41,202
-No he didn't, that's the thing. It was...
-I'm sorry.

830
01:08:41,226 --> 01:08:42,850
-What's that?
-May I?

831
01:08:44,018 --> 01:08:46,933
-Please excuse me.
-Well, that...

832
01:08:49,850 --> 01:08:52,577
-One moment, how much are these liqueurs?
-4 schillings.

833
01:08:52,601 --> 01:08:54,268
-Both of them?
-8 schillings.

834
01:08:54,934 --> 01:08:57,603
Then bring me... one more.

835
01:09:18,518 --> 01:09:23,934
♫ My dearest I'm in love with your perfume

836
01:09:24,683 --> 01:09:28,976
♫ Because it puts me in the right mood

837
01:09:29,809 --> 01:09:33,576
Auntie, I don't get it.
Why shouldn't I call him?

838
01:09:33,600 --> 01:09:39,850
-Because it is not proper.
-Why not? The poor guy's taking inventory.

839
01:09:39,975 --> 01:09:45,226
♫ My dearest, I'm so fond of your perfume

840
01:09:46,018 --> 01:09:50,184
♫ It brings us together,
even when you're far away

841
01:09:51,100 --> 01:09:54,392
♫ It smells of kisses that...

842
01:09:55,475 --> 01:09:58,143
-I am going to call him!
-Kitty!

843
01:09:58,726 --> 01:09:59,808
Yes, I'm calling him.

844
01:10:18,933 --> 01:10:23,225
-Hello! Help!
-What? What happened?

845
01:10:23,311 --> 01:10:28,770
-Help! The rascal locked me in!
-I'll call the police immediately!

846
01:10:29,476 --> 01:10:33,850
♫ My dearest I'm in love with your perfume

847
01:10:34,393 --> 01:10:38,600
♫ Because it puts me in the right mood

848
01:10:38,725 --> 01:10:42,683
♫ I don't know what it is,
I only realize

849
01:10:43,018 --> 01:10:47,185
♫ There's something, there's something,
there's something

850
01:10:49,101 --> 01:10:54,392
You left me here... Terrible, that noise!

851
01:10:54,601 --> 01:10:57,852
-By the way, we were interrupted.
-Yes, we were.

852
01:10:58,143 --> 01:11:03,785
-What is it you wanted to say?
-I... Impossible with this music.

853
01:11:03,809 --> 01:11:07,809
It's about... Thank heavens!

854
01:11:08,228 --> 01:11:10,018
It's about making a dream come...

855
01:11:12,018 --> 01:11:13,142
Here we go again.

856
01:11:13,893 --> 01:11:15,892
It's about making a dream come true.

857
01:11:17,311 --> 01:11:21,159
-May I have this dance?
-I don't know.

858
01:11:21,183 --> 01:11:25,768
I beg you. You can't deny me this waltz.
Ain't I right, Sir?

859
01:11:28,018 --> 01:11:29,439
-Please excuse me.
-Thank you.

860
01:11:47,226 --> 01:11:50,701
-I'm sorry... Hey there, you!
-What do you want?

861
01:11:50,725 --> 01:11:55,017
-All this dance music all the time!
-Of course, this is a dance bar.

862
01:11:55,772 --> 01:11:59,392
-The orchestra plays whatever one wants?
-Yes, why not?

863
01:11:59,726 --> 01:12:02,398
Then tell them to play rummy for a while.

864
01:12:13,101 --> 01:12:14,897
Hello! Is anybody here?

865
01:12:16,018 --> 01:12:19,059
Look over there. Someone's knocking.

866
01:12:19,434 --> 01:12:20,975
Turn on the light!

867
01:12:27,518 --> 01:12:29,577
-Hands in the air!
-I beg your pardon?

868
01:12:29,601 --> 01:12:31,539
-Hands in the air!
-But I'm the owner!

869
01:12:31,563 --> 01:12:33,767
-Anyone could say that.
-Good evening.

870
01:12:34,018 --> 01:12:39,481
Good evening. My good friend,
am I the owner or ain't I?

871
01:12:39,767 --> 01:12:41,309
-Does he tell the truth?
-Of course.

872
01:12:41,851 --> 01:12:45,392
-Why didn't you say so earlier?
-Earlier? I couldn't get a word in!

873
01:12:46,350 --> 01:12:48,836
And what are you doing in there?
Who locked you in?

874
01:12:48,860 --> 01:12:51,310
My partner played a stupid joke on me.

875
01:12:51,642 --> 01:12:54,536
Unbelievable! Calling the cops for that?

876
01:12:54,560 --> 01:12:57,725
I could've died of hunger in there.
Maybe that's what you...

877
01:12:58,058 --> 01:12:59,729
-Where's Bobby?
-And who are you?

878
01:13:00,017 --> 01:13:03,494
-I called here just now.
-So you were the one setting me free!

879
01:13:03,518 --> 01:13:06,518
So where is Bobby? What did you do to him?

880
01:13:07,600 --> 01:13:10,410
I to him? He to me! He locked me in!

881
01:13:10,434 --> 01:13:13,744
Unbelievable. Let me tell you something.

882
01:13:13,768 --> 01:13:17,826
I'll report you for
deceiving the authorities. On with it!

883
01:13:17,850 --> 01:13:23,451
-Now you see what my partner is up to.
-Your partner? He's your partner?

884
01:13:23,475 --> 01:13:26,536
-Of course!
-He told me he'd be working here all night.

885
01:13:26,560 --> 01:13:30,309
Working my ass. He's at the Moulin Rouge,
with my girl.

886
01:13:30,725 --> 01:13:36,142
Enough dancing already. Now we need to
have a talk before the music starts again.

887
01:13:36,851 --> 01:13:42,809
-I... My friend thinks, in our business...
-May I?

888
01:13:45,184 --> 01:13:47,309
Excuse me, may I?

889
01:13:51,976 --> 01:13:57,143
Finally, he's left. So, my friend thinks,
we need a woman in our business.

890
01:13:57,601 --> 01:14:00,535
-Do you want to be a boss at our firm?
-Me?

891
01:14:00,559 --> 01:14:08,142
He told you lots of silly stuff, probably.
But the gist of it, the transaction...

892
01:14:08,684 --> 01:14:13,642
-...he doesn't know anything about that.
-But I'm no transaction.

893
01:14:14,184 --> 01:14:17,327
Well, to me, a few 100.000s schillings
feels like business.

894
01:14:17,351 --> 01:14:19,392
It's not a lot, but we'll take it.

895
01:14:20,268 --> 01:14:22,243
What are you talking about?

896
01:14:22,267 --> 01:14:28,726
I'm talking about the money you might...
would invest in our business. Charmingly...

897
01:14:28,975 --> 01:14:31,726
Me? But I don't have any money.

898
01:14:35,475 --> 01:14:38,142
That's something else.
A millionairess and no money?

899
01:14:38,808 --> 01:14:42,809
Millionairess? But I'm no millionairess!

900
01:14:43,601 --> 01:14:48,601
-But you advertised!
-Not that I'm a millionairess!

901
01:14:49,226 --> 01:14:54,284
Don't fool around! Are you Longing 202
or aren't you Longing 202?

902
01:14:54,308 --> 01:14:58,725
-Of course I'm Longing 202!
-I knew it. Here, read this.

903
01:14:59,101 --> 01:15:01,517
"Lady worth millions..."

904
01:15:01,851 --> 01:15:06,685
-Unbelievable! That's a terrible mistake!
-What do you mean?

905
01:15:07,892 --> 01:15:15,102
-I never advertised this!
-Oh my... You don't have any money?

906
01:15:15,225 --> 01:15:18,243
-No!
-Mrs., you are a swindler!

907
01:15:18,267 --> 01:15:21,435
-How dare you!
-Stay on your seat, don't make a scene!

908
01:15:22,018 --> 01:15:28,558
Now I get it. That's why you hired me.

909
01:15:29,058 --> 01:15:33,779
And that's why you were so nice to me!
And that's why your friend asked me out!

910
01:15:34,058 --> 01:15:37,851
-What a nerve!
-She must be jealous.

911
01:15:44,309 --> 01:15:46,684
-Shame on you!
-What's going on?

912
01:15:47,183 --> 01:15:49,643
-Leave me be!
-Magda!

913
01:15:51,310 --> 01:15:56,035
Here he is, the scoundrel! Making a date
with me and going out with another girl.

914
01:15:56,059 --> 01:15:58,808
-Why are you here, Kitty?
-Why am I here? For this!

915
01:16:02,517 --> 01:16:03,850
Thanks a lot.

916
01:16:12,350 --> 01:16:15,159
Well hello Harry! How did you escape?

917
01:16:15,183 --> 01:16:19,225
You're the most insolent guy I ever met.

918
01:16:19,768 --> 01:16:22,284
-You've got me into trouble again.
-Me?

919
01:16:22,308 --> 01:16:27,202
-We'll talk about it at home. Just wait.
-Forget it, we're no longer friends.

920
01:16:27,226 --> 01:16:30,934
-From now on you mean nothing to me.
-That's right.

921
01:16:30,976 --> 01:16:37,684
You're mean less than nothing to me.
Vacuum, negative space, black hole.

922
01:16:38,809 --> 01:16:42,309
What's that? Heavens, now it starts...

923
01:16:42,808 --> 01:16:47,160
♫ The sky over Vienna

924
01:16:47,184 --> 01:16:51,434
♫ Is twice as nice as anywhere else

925
01:16:51,933 --> 01:16:55,184
♫ Because the whole year long

926
01:16:55,225 --> 01:16:58,308
♫ The sky is full of clouds

927
01:17:00,101 --> 01:17:05,309
♫ A Viennese looks at stars
from the office

928
01:17:06,310 --> 01:17:11,352
♫ While thinking about all the
unpaid debts

929
01:17:11,642 --> 01:17:13,684
Splitter, stop the singing!
That's terrible!

930
01:17:15,301 --> 01:17:18,850
-Splitter, please continue. Beautiful!
-Thank you.

931
